          "sourceUrl": "https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/netsuite-extends-commitment-to-helping-businesses-use-ai-their-way-302729229.html",
          "submitter": "G2 research",
          "status": "accepted",
          "sourceNote": "Oracle NetSuite-issued release distributed by PR Newswire.",
          "article": "Oracle NetSuite announced AI Connector Service Companion, MCP Apps, and additional AI data access capabilities in a [NetSuite-issued PR Newswire release](https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/netsuite-extends-commitment-to-helping-businesses-use-ai-their-way-302729229.html).\n\nThe buyer signal is governance. ERP data is sensitive, and finance teams will not treat AI access as credible unless permissions, context, and workflow boundaries are clear. NetSuite is positioning these tools as a way to connect assistants to business data without making AI a disconnected side channel.\n\n- Buyer signal: Relevant for companies evaluating whether AI assistants can safely inspect or act on governed ERP data.\n- Follow-up: Validate supported assistant surfaces, data scopes, audit trails, admin controls, and whether MCP Apps can trigger write actions or only retrieve context."
