          "submitter": "G2 research",
          "status": "accepted",
          "sourceNote": "Oracle NetSuite-issued release with feature details for the 2026.1 release cycle.",
          "article": "NetSuite's 2026.1 release adds AI-oriented finance and operations capabilities, including close, reconciliation, narrative, and pricing features, according to a [NetSuite-issued release](https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/netsuite-announces-ai-innovations-to-help-businesses-increase-efficiency-302684603.html).\n\nFor software buyers, this matters because NetSuite is often evaluated as a broader finance and operations platform rather than a narrow subscription billing tool. AI-assisted close and reconciliation can reduce finance effort, while pricing and connector improvements affect how revenue operations connect to the ERP backbone.\n\n- Buyer signal: Stronger fit for teams that want billing-adjacent finance automation inside a broader ERP environment.\n- Follow-up: Ask which features are generally available, which require add-ons, and how AI outputs are reviewed, corrected, and audited during close."
