          "sourceLabel": "PayPal Newsroom",
          "sourceUrl": "https://newsroom.paypal-corp.com/2026-02-25-Rainforest-Launches-Embedded-PayPal-Integration-for-Vertical-Software-Platforms",
          "submitter": "G2 research",
          "status": "accepted",
          "sourceNote": "Official PayPal corporate newsroom release.",
          "article": "Rainforest launched an embedded PayPal integration for vertical software platforms, according to PayPal's [corporate newsroom release](https://newsroom.paypal-corp.com/2026-02-25-Rainforest-Launches-Embedded-PayPal-Integration-for-Vertical-Software-Platforms).\n\nThe buyer angle is distribution. Vertical SaaS companies often need to let merchants accept familiar payment methods without becoming payment infrastructure companies themselves. PayPal, Venmo, Pay Later, cards, Apple Pay, and Pay by Bank support can matter when the buyer is building merchant-facing workflows.\n\n- Buyer signal: PayPal remains relevant as an embedded payment option for platforms, not only as a consumer checkout brand.\n- Follow-up: Compare onboarding, merchant underwriting, settlement, fees, dispute handling, and how embedded PayPal payments connect to invoicing or subscription flows."
