          "sourceUrl": "https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/paypal-brings-together-developers-ai-leaders-to-power-agentic-commerce-at-dev-days-302441418.html",
          "submitter": "G2 research",
          "status": "accepted",
          "sourceNote": "PayPal-issued release distributed by PR Newswire.",
          "article": "PayPal announced developer tools for agentic commerce in a [PayPal-issued PR Newswire release](https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/paypal-brings-together-developers-ai-leaders-to-power-agentic-commerce-at-dev-days-302441418.html).\n\nThe near-term subscription billing tie is exploratory but important. As AI agents start initiating purchases, checking order status, or creating payment links, finance and product teams will need payment tools that are explicit about authorization, user intent, and transaction control.\n\n- Buyer signal: Relevant for teams thinking about how AI agents may interact with invoicing and payment workflows.\n- Follow-up: Ask what is production-ready, what safeguards exist for agent-initiated actions, and how PayPal distinguishes discovery, authorization, and payment execution."
