      "key": "square-point-of-sale-2026-06-25-square-ships-pos-improvements-for-alerts-variation-controls-audio-cues-and-item-grids",
      "date": "2026-06-25",
      "type": "feature-update",
      "headline": "Square ships POS improvements for alerts, variation controls, audio cues, and item grids",
      "buyerRelevance": "Good signal for busy sellers comparing POS speed, staff workflow, and online-order handling.",
      "sourceLabel": "Square Feature Log",
      "sourceUrl": "https://squareup.com/us/en/feature-log",
      "submitter": "G2 research",
      "status": "accepted",
      "sourceNote": "Official Square changelog with dated POS feature entries.",
      "article": "Square's [feature log](https://squareup.com/us/en/feature-log) lists POS improvements around alerts, variation controls, audio cues, and item grids.\n\nThis is not subscription billing in the narrow sense, but it is useful buyer context for businesses comparing commerce operations. POS updates affect speed at the counter, staff workflow, online-order awareness, and how quickly sellers can find or configure items during a rush.\n\n- Buyer signal: Square keeps investing in day-to-day seller workflow, which can matter more to retailers and restaurants than back-office billing depth.\n- Follow-up: Evaluate whether the improvements apply to the buyer's Square plan, hardware, industry mode, and staff permissions model.",
      "productSlug": "square-point-of-sale",
